  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (01325bc 2022-08-03T00:04:48.802271Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nexport FOUNDRY_FUZZ_RUNS=10000 && forge test --match testInt96 -vvvvv\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI have recently encountered an issue with fuzzing int96 parameters, our current workaround is using int256 and bounding it between the min and max values of int96.\r\n\r\nIn a newly initialized `forge init`. \r\nAdded a function in `Contract.t.sol`:\r\n`function testInt96(int256 flowRate) public {}`\r\n\r\nRan: `export FOUNDRY_FUZZ_RUNS=10000 && forge test --match testInt96 -vvvvv`\r\n\r\nError: \r\n```\r\n[FAIL. Reason: EvmError: Revert. Counterexample: calldata=0x9fb3171a0000000000000000000000000000000000000000800000000000000000000000, args=[39614081257132168796771975168]] testFlowDataEncoding(int96) (runs: 438, μ: 276, ~: 276)\r\nTraces:\r\n  [238] ConstantFlowAgreementV1Properties::testFlowDataEncoding(39614081257132168796771975168)\r\n    └─ ← \"EvmError: Revert\"\r\n\r\nTest result: FAILED. 0 passed; 1 failed; finished in 18.07ms\r\n\r\nFailed tests:\r\n[FAIL. Reason: EvmError: Revert. Counterexample: calldata=0x9fb3171a0000000000000000000000000000000000000000800000000000000000000000, args=[39614081257132168796771975168]] testFlowDataEncoding(int96) (runs: 438, μ: 276, ~: 276)\r\n```",
